    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_014_0550_8__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card references 'lfcShrink()' function and three named shrinkage estimators (apeglm, normal, ashr) that are not mentioned in the 2014 DESeq2 paper. These appear to be features added in later versions of DESeq2 (likely post-2014).",
        "The card specifies the 'airway dataset' and a 'treated-vs-untreated contrast', which are not discussed in this paper. The paper uses the Bottomly et al. and Pickrell et al. datasets for benchmarking.",
        "The paper describes DESeq2's default shrinkage approach using an empirical Bayes zero-centered normal prior, but does not discuss alternative shrinkage estimators or a function to switch between them."
