    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_014_0550_8__task_003/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate task card describes a workflow for importing transcript-level quantification data (from Salmon via tximport) into DESeq2. The paper is the DESeq2 method paper (Love et al. 2014), which focuses on the statistical methods for differential expression analysis of count data, not on upstream data import workflows.",
        "The paper does not discuss tximport, Salmon, or any transcript-level quantification tools. It assumes count data are already available as input.",
        "The paper does not describe DESeqDataSet object construction or the DESeqDataSetFromTximport function.",
        "This task card appears to describe a modern DESeq2 workflow (tximport integration) that postdates or is orthogonal to the core DESeq2 method paper."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 4,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:16:18.725884+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_014_0550_8__task_004/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DESeq2 uses the average expression strength of each gene, across all samples, as its filter criterion, and it omits all genes with mean normalized counts below a filtering threshold from multiple testing adjustment. DESeq2 by default will choose a threshold that maximizes the number of genes found at a user-specified target FDR.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes automatic independent filtering based on mean normalized counts as a core feature of DESeq2.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the results() function automatically perform independent filtering based on mean normalized counts, and what are the expected outputs when this filtering is applied to DESeq2 results?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:16:31.991077+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_014_0550_8__task_004/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DESeq2 reports the standard error for each shrunken LFC estimate... For significance testing, DESeq2 uses a Wald test... The Wald test P values from the subset of genes that pass an independent filtering step... are adjusted for multiple testing using the procedure of Benjamini and Hochberg.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms DESeq2 outputs log2 fold changes (LFCs), p-values, and adjusted p-values with independent filtering applied.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Results table with log2 fold changes, p-values, and adjusted p-values after automatic independent filtering (default alpha=0.1)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:16:31.991077+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
