    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1186_s13059_014_0550_8__task_004/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The title references apeglm's nbinomC fast mode and the pasilla dataset, neither of which appear in the DESeq2 paper. This suggests the task card may be conflating DESeq2 with a different paper or tutorial.",
        "The expected outputs include IHW-adjusted p-values, but IHW is not a DESeq2 feature described in this paper. IHW is a separate R package for independent hypothesis weighting that can be used downstream of DESeq2 but is not part of DESeq2 itself.",
        "The research question is well-grounded in the paper's content (independent filtering), but the expected outputs and title diverge significantly from what the paper actually describes."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
