      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it to compare shrinkage-based estimates across estimator types (apeglm adaptive t-prior, normal adaptive prior, ashr mixture-of-normals) to assess robustness of effect size inference.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:18:48.715144+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/count-data-normalization-rna-seq/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The starting point of a DESeq2 analysis is a count matrix K with one row for each gene i and one column for each sample j... For many applications, the same constant s j can be used for all genes in a sample, which then accounts for differences in sequencing depth between samples. To estimate these size factors, the DESeq2 package offers the median-of-ratios method",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes normalization via size factors to account for sequencing depth differences before differential expression analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "count-data-normalization-rna-seq",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Normalize raw RNA-seq read counts to account for sequencing depth and library composition differences before differential expression testing",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:19:02.951552+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/count-data-normalization-rna-seq/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To estimate these size factors, the DESeq2 package offers the median-of-ratios method already used in DESeq [4]... The DESeq2 package is available at http://www.bioconductor.org/packages/release/bioc/html/DESeq2.html",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms DESeq2 implements median-of-ratios normalization and is available as R/Bioconductor package.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "count-data-normalization-rna-seq",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "DESeq2 performs median-of-ratios normalization via size factor estimation and differential expression testing on normalized counts",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:19:02.951552+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
