      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/results-table-extraction-and-comparison/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DESeq2 overcomes this issue by shrinking LFC estimates toward zero in a manner such that shrinkage is stronger when the available information for a gene is low... we first perform ordinary GLM fits to obtain maximum-likelihood estimates (MLEs) for the LFCs and then fit a zero-centered normal distribution to the observed distribution of MLEs over all genes. This distribution is used as a prior on LFCs in a second round of GLM fits, and the MAP estimates are kept as final estimates of LFC.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported. Paper explicitly describes empirical Bayes shrinkage with zero-centered normal prior for LFC estimation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "results-table-extraction-and-comparison",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "methods",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Empirical Bayes shrinkage for fold-change estimation using zero-centered normal prior",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:22:10.912211+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/results-table-extraction-and-comparison/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Furthermore, a standard error for each estimate is reported, which is derived from the posterior's curvature at its maximum... These shrunken LFCs and their standard errors are used in the Wald tests for differential expression... The Wald test P values from the subset of genes that pass an independent filtering step... are adjusted for multiple testing using the procedure of Benjamini and Hochberg.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported. Paper describes output of shrunken LFCs with standard errors and adjusted p-values.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "results-table-extraction-and-comparison",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Shrunken log fold change estimates, p-values, and adjusted p-values for each gene across conditions",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:22:10.912211+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rna-seq-differential-expression-analysis/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We present DESeq2, a method for differential analysis of count data, using shrinkage estimation for dispersions and fold changes to improve stability and interpretability of estimates... We model read counts K ij as following a negative binomial distribution... with mean \u03bc ij and dispersion \u03b1 i.",
      "asbval:note": "Core claim fully supported by abstract and methods sections.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rna-seq-differential-expression-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply DESeq2's negative binomial generalized linear models to quantify differential gene expression between experimental conditions, producing shrunken log fold change estimates and significance tests.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
