    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "ashr is not mentioned in the paper. Paper discusses DESeq2's own empirical Bayes shrinkage for fold changes but does not mention ashr. Paper does mention GFOLD as an alternative shrinkage method: 'We note that other Bayesian efforts toward moderating fold changes for RNA-seq include hierarchical models [8,19] and the GFOLD (or generalized fold change) tool [20]' but not ashr.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ashr \u2014 Adaptive Shrinkage for stabilizing fold-change estimates via empirical Bayes shrinkage",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:23:00.719109+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The starting point of a DESeq2 analysis is a count matrix K with one row for each gene i and one column for each sample j. The matrix entries K ij indicate the number of sequencing reads that have been unambiguously mapped to a gene in a sample... Other methods to obtain count matrices include the htseq-count script [62] and the Bioconductor packages easyRNASeq [63] and featureCounts [64].",
      "asbval:note": "Count matrix format and input sources confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input is count matrix (genes \u00d7 samples, integer values from HTSeq, featureCounts, or similar)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:23:00.719109+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The count matrix and metadata, including the gene model and sample information, are stored in an S4 class derived from the SummarizedExperiment class",
      "asbval:note": "Metadata requirement confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Sample metadata table with condition/batch covariate required",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:23:00.719109+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Note that although we refer in this paper to counts of reads in genes, the methods presented here can be applied as well to other kinds of HTS count data... [but] the methods presented here can be applied as well to other kinds of HTS count data [implying raw counts are required]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper emphasizes count data requirement; normalized data would violate the negative binomial model assumptions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input is already normalized expression matrix or continuous abundance (e.g., TPM, FPKM)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:23:00.719109+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/rnaseq-count-matrix-analysis/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Small replicate numbers, discreteness, large dynamic range and the presence of outliers require a suitable statistical approach... a core challenge is the small number of samples in typical HTS experiments \u2013 often as few as two or three replicates per condition.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper acknowledges challenges with small sample sizes; dispersion estimation is critical and becomes unreliable with very few replicates.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
