    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sample-metadata-preparation-and-assignment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The count matrix for this dataset was downloaded from the Re Count online resource [27]. This dataset offers more subtle differences between conditions than the Bottomly et al. [16] dataset... The starting point of a DESeq2 analysis is a count matrix K with one row for each gene i and one column for each sample j.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes DESeq2 analysis workflow and design matrices but does not explicitly discuss colData construction or SummarizedExperiment/DESeqDataSet object creation. The paper focuses on statistical methods rather than practical data structure preparation. The claim about 'colData' as a named object and its assignment to DESeqDataSet is not found in the paper passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "sample-metadata-preparation-and-assignment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct a sample metadata table (colData) that maps sample identifiers to experimental conditions and covariates, then assign it as the column-level annotation for a DESeqDataSet. This is a prerequisite for differential expression testing, as DESeq2 uses metadata to define the ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:23:17.225678+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sample-metadata-preparation-and-assignment/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "DESeq2 is implemented as a package for the R statistical environment and is available [10] as part of the Bioconductor project [11]. The count matrix and metadata, including the gene model and sample information, are stored in an S4 class derived from the Summarized-Experiment class of the Genomic Ranges package [60].",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms DESeq2 uses metadata and SummarizedExperiment classes, and mentions design matrices extensively. However, the specific function names (DESeqDataSetFromMatrix, DESeqDataSetFromTximport, DESeqDataSet constructors) are not mentioned in the passages. The paper does not name these constructor functions explicitly.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "sample-metadata-preparation-and-assignment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "DESeq2 \u2014 Accepts colData as input to DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(), DESeqDataSetFromTximport(), and DESeqDataSet() constructors; uses metadata to define design formula and specify contrasts",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:23:17.225678+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
