      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The DESeq2 package is available at http://www.bioconductor.org/packages/release/bioc/html/DESeq2.html",
      "asbval:note": "DESeq2 is confirmed in the paper as the primary tool for differential expression analysis of count data. However, the paper does not mention DESeqDataSetFromTximport() or any tximport integration. The paper describes DESeq2 as accepting count matrices but does not detail specific constructor functions for tximport output.",
