    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_046",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Variance stabilizing transformation and rlog are used to remove the dependence of variance on the mean.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "The point of these two transformations, the VST and the *rlog*,\nis to remove the dependence of the variance on the mean,\nparticularly the high variance of the logarithm of count data when the\nmean is low.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_046",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_047",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "VST and rlog produce transformed data on the log2 scale which has been normalized with respect to library size.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "Both transformations produce transformed data on the log2 scale\nwhich has been normalized with respect to library size or other\nnormalization factors.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_047",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_048",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "The rlog function may take too long for experiments with many samples (e.g. 100s), so vst is a faster choice.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "if you have many samples (e.g. 100s),\nthe *rlog* function might take too long, and so the *vst* function\nwill be a faster choice.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_048",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_049",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "The rlog function requires fitting a shrinkage term for each sample and each gene which takes time.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "The rlog and VST have similar properties, but the rlog requires\nfitting a shrinkage term for each sample and each gene which takes\ntime.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_049",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_050",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Transformation functions vst and rlog have a blind argument for whether transformation should be blind to sample information.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "The two functions, *vst* and *rlog* have an argument\n`blind`, for whether the transformation should be blind to the\nsample information specified by the design formula.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_050",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_051",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "When blind equals TRUE, vst and rlog functions re-estimate dispersions using only an intercept.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "When\n`blind` equals `TRUE` (the default), the functions\nwill re-estimate the dispersions using only an intercept.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_051",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_052",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Blind dispersion estimation should be used to compare samples in a manner unbiased by experimental groups for quality assurance.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "This setting should be used in order to compare\nsamples in a manner wholly unbiased by the information about\nexperimental groups, for example to perform sample QA (quality\nassurance)",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_052",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_053",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Blind dispersion estimation is not appropriate when expecting many genes will have large differences explainable by experimental design.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "However, blind dispersion estimation is not the appropriate choice if\none expects that many or the majority of genes (rows) will have large\ndifferences in counts which are explainable by the experimental design,\nand one wishes to transform the data for downstream analysis.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_053",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_054",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Using blind dispersion estimation can lead to overly shrinking transformed values when design differences are misattributed as noise.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "In this\ncase, using blind dispersion estimation will lead to large estimates\nof dispersion, as it attributes differences due to experimental design\nas unwanted *noise*, and will result in overly shrinking the transformed\nvalues towards each other.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_054",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_055",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Setting blind to FALSE uses dispersions already estimated or estimates them using the current design formula.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "By setting `blind` to `FALSE`, the dispersions\nalready estimated will be used to perform transformations, or if not\npresent, they will be estimated using the current design formula.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_055",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:15:17.830770+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/claim/claim_056",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:claim_text": "Transformation functions vst and rlog return an object of class DESeqTransform, which is a subclass of RangedSummarizedExperiment.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-014-0550-8",
      "asbval:source_excerpt": "These transformation functions return an object of class *DESeqTransform*\nwhich is a subclass of *RangedSummarizedExperiment*.",
      "asbval:substring_in_paper": false,
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "claim_056",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "ledger_claim",
